[4] Regional updates: South Asia
[A] Bangladesh
Date: Thu 23 Sep 2021 5:16 PM BST
Source: The Daily Star, Star Digital Report [edited]
https://www.thedailystar.net/health/disease/coronavirus/events-who/deaths-infections/news/covid-19-24-dead-1144-new-cases-24-hours-2182531


According to a press release issued by the Directorate General of Health Services (DGHS), 24 people have died of COVID-19 in 24 hours (as of 8 am today [23 Sep 2021]).

With them, the total number of deaths reached 27 337 and the death rate stands at 1.77%.

At least 1144 new infections were recorded in the meantime, taking the total number of people infected to 1 548 320, added the release.

The current positivity rate is 4.61% while the total positivity rate stands at 16.21%.

A total of 24 820 samples were tested across the country in 24 hours (until 8 am today [23 Sep 2021]).

At least 1653 COVID-19 patients have recovered in this period. The total number of recoveries now stands at 1 507 789 and the recovery rate at 97.38%.

Among the 24 deceased, 10 were men and 14 women. Of them 2 were between 21-30 years old, 2 were within 31-40; 2 were between 41-50; 7 within 51-60, 7 were within 61-70, and 4 between 71-80 years old, added the release.

