Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 23 Sep 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20SEPT24_1632599084.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 40.3% of daily case numbers and 51.7% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 88.84 million cases. The USA reported over 121 000 cases in the last 24 hours, followed by Brazil (36 473) and Mexico (11 603). 6 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 5 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 34.0% of daily case numbers and 25.9% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 69.09 million. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium, Switzerland (1 case), and Kazakhstan, among others. 23 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 10 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 6.9% of daily case numbers and 7.5% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 15.57 million cases. Many countries including Iran, Morocco, Jordan, Tunisia, Lebanon, Egypt among others, did not report any cases over the last 24 hours. Iraq reported the highest number of cases followed by Pakistan and Libya.

- The African region reported 2.2% of daily case numbers and 4.1% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.98 million cases. South Africa (2783), reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Botswana, and Ethiopia.

- The Western Pacific region reported 11.4% of daily case numbers and 8.1% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 8.16 million cases. Philippines, reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 17 000 cases), followed by Malaysia, Vietnam, Japan, Mongolia, South Korea, Australia, Singapore, and Cambodia.

- The South East Asia region reported 10.4% of the daily newly reported cases and 8.5% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 42.74 million cases. India is dominant reporting over 31 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (12 697), Indonesia (2557), Myanmar (1667), Bangladesh (1233), and Nepal (1103). Sri Lanka and Maldives have not reported any cases for the last several days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 24 Sep 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

